UI Styling Instructions

1. Dark Theme Base
	•	Set background color of the entire dashboard to: #1E1E2F
	•	Set all text color to: #FFFFFF (or a soft white like #E0E0E0 for subtler contrast)

⸻

2. Button Styling
	•	Filter Buttons (Today, 7 Days, 30 Days, Custom Range)
	•	Background color: #2A2A3B
	•	Hover color: #3A3A4A
	•	Text color: #FFFFFF
	•	Border radius: 6px
	•	Font weight: medium or semi-bold

⸻

3. Job Details Table
	•	Background: #2A2A3B
	•	Header text: #CCCCCC
	•	Row text: #FFFFFF
	•	Border radius: 8px
	•	Add some padding: padding: 12px

Status Pill Colors:
	•	Success:
	•	Background: #1F8A70
	•	Text: #FFFFFF
	•	Failure:
	•	Background: #B00020
	•	Text: #FFFFFF

⸻

4. Donut Chart (Job Status Overview)
	•	Success color: #1F8A70
	•	Failure color: #B00020
	•	Inner text: #FFFFFF
	•	Background: transparent or same as dashboard background #1E1E2F

⸻

5. Cards & Panels
	•	Each section (Filters, Job Overview, Job Details) should be in a card-like container:
	•	Background: #2A2A3B
	•	Border radius: 12px
	•	Shadow: subtle (box-shadow: 0px 2px 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.3))

⸻

6. Font
	•	Use a clean sans-serif font like 'Inter', 'Segoe UI', or 'Roboto'
	•	Use consistent font sizes:
	•	Title: 20px, bold
	•	Section labels: 16px, semi-bold
	•	Regular text: 14px
